<h4>Course Descriptions:</h4>

<div class="course-cont">
  <div class="course">
    <span class="course-arrow">&raquo;</span> <div class="course-title"><h4>INT601 The Globalization of World Politics</h4></div>
    <div class="course-descr">
      This course is an examination of several current world problems with a focus on creating world order. It is an introductory
      course into the political science subdiscipline of international relations. There are no prerequisites. It examines current
      world problems and attempts to achieve global governance of these problems in the context of international relations, international
      organizations and international politics. In the process of this examination, you will develop the knowledge and skills necessary
      to analyze the ethical and political impact of international society and international organizations on efforts made by the
      international community to resolve those problems. The aim of this course is to provide the students with an overview of
      contemporary world politics. We will focus on definition and scope of IR, brief history of IR, major theories of IR,
      international security, international political economy, diplomacy, international organizations, global trade and finance,
      environmental issues, human rights, gender issues, regionalism, integration, nationalism, nuclear proliferation, etc.
    </div>
  </div>
