    <span class="course-arrow">&raquo;</span> <div class="course-title"><h4>INT602 Kyrgyz Politics and Foreign Policy</h4></div>
    <div class="course-descr">
      This class provides an introduction to contemporary research on politics and foreign policy of Kyrgyzstan.
      The course is structured in three parts. In the first part we review political dynamics in Kyrgyzstan.
      In the second we turn to regional politics in Central Asian region. In the final section we analyze Kyrgyz
      foreign policy.
      The major questions to be addressed by the course are: What are the main elements of politics and foreign
      policy in Central Asian region and Kyrgyzstan? How central is politics to economic development in Kyrgyzstan?
      How do Kyrgyz political and social networks determine political choices? How do economic structures in turn
      impact on politics? How important are international effects relative to domestic political features?
